properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued February 17 at 6:36PM CST until February 17 at 9:00PM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
...Heavy Snow To Impact Travel Through the Evening...

.A slow moving band of snow moving eastward across eastern
Minnesota through western Wisconsin will produce snowfall rates
of 1 to 2 inches per hour through early this evening. A Winter
Storm Warning remains in effect for Sibley and Nicollet counties,
which will see a couple more hours of heavy snow, and could have
localized 7 to 10 inches by the time the snow ends this evening.

East of the warning, from the Twin Cities metro south to the Iowa
border, periods of snow, occasionally heavy at times, will
continue to fall this evening. A Winter Weather Advisory remains
in effect for most areas along and east of a line from the Twin
Cities metro to Blue Earth. Snowfall amounts of 2 to 4 inches may
be common across the advisory area, with localized amounts of
around 6 inches possible. The snow will end by 9 PM in west
central Wisconsin.

* WHAT...Heavy snow. Total snow accumulations of 5 to 7 inches,
with highly localized amounts of up to 9 inches possible.

* WHERE...Sibley and Nicollet Counties.

* WHEN...Until 9 PM CST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 PM CST THIS EVENING
